---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Us | LaTech Editorial Publishing"
  description="Learn about our mission to advance rigorous scholarship and make knowledge accessible through editorial excellence and writing support."
>
  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>About LaTech Editorial Publishing</h1>
      <p class="page-subtitle">
        Our mission, vision, and commitment to editorial excellence
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="narrow-content">
      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Our Mission</h2>
        <p>
          LaTech Editorial Publishing exists to bridge the gap between rigorous
          academic research and public understanding. We publish scholarly work
          that meets the highest standards of intellectual rigor while making
          knowledge accessible to diverse audiences.
        </p>
        <p>
          Founded in 2024, we recognized a critical need: too much valuable research
          remains locked behind paywalls or buried in academic jargon, inaccessible
          to the very communities it could benefit. We set out to change that by
          creating a platform where rigorous scholarship meets clear communication,
          where peer review ensures quality, and where knowledge serves the public good.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our work is guided by a simple principle: excellent research deserves
          excellent communication. We believe that complexity should not mean
          inaccessibility, and that the most important ideas should reach the
          widest possible audience without sacrificing intellectual integrity.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Our Vision</h2>
        <p>
          We envision a world where quality scholarship is not locked behind
          paywalls, where emerging researchers receive the mentorship they need,
          and where informed public discourse is grounded in evidence and
          expertise.
        </p>
        <p>
          In this vision, academic research contributes meaningfully to public
          understanding. Scholars communicate clearly without compromising rigor.
          Emerging researchers find supportive communities and constructive feedback.
          And readers everywhere have access to well-researched, thoughtfully
          presented information that helps them make sense of complex issues.
        </p>
        <p>
          We're building toward a publishing ecosystem that values both intellectual
          excellence and public service—where the best research reaches the people
          who need it most, regardless of their institutional affiliation or ability
          to pay subscription fees.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>What We Publish</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Scholarly articles and research:</strong> Peer-reviewed work that
            advances knowledge across disciplines
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Editorial analysis and commentary:</strong> Thoughtful pieces
            that connect research to broader conversations
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Educational resources and guides:</strong> Practical tools for
            researchers and writers
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Editorial Independence</h2>
        <p>
          Our editorial decisions are made solely on the basis of quality,
          rigor, and relevance. We maintain strict independence from commercial,
          political, and institutional pressures. All content undergoes rigorous
          review processes to ensure it meets our standards for accuracy,
          clarity, and intellectual contribution.
        </p>
        <p>
          This independence is fundamental to our mission. We do not accept
          sponsored content. We do not allow funders or partners to influence
          editorial decisions. We publish work based on its merit, not its
          alignment with any particular agenda or institution.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our peer review process ensures that scholarly articles meet rigorous
          academic standards. Our editorial review ensures that all content,
          whether scholarly or editorial, meets our standards for clarity,
          accuracy, and contribution to public understanding. This dual commitment
          to rigor and accessibility sets us apart.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Who We Serve</h2>
        <p>
          Our community includes diverse individuals united by a commitment to
          rigorous scholarship and accessible communication:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Researchers and academics</strong> seeking to share their work
            beyond traditional academic circles, reaching practitioners, policymakers,
            and the broader public
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Graduate students and emerging scholars</strong> developing their
            voices and seeking constructive feedback on their work, mentorship in
            academic writing, and opportunities to publish
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Writers and communicators</strong> seeking to translate complex
            research into accessible formats, whether for public audiences, professional
            communities, or educational purposes
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>General readers</strong> interested in well-researched, accessible
            information on topics ranging from education and research methods to
            public policy and social issues
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Educators and practitioners</strong> looking for evidence-based
            resources to inform their work and share with their communities
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Our Values</h2>
        <p>
          Everything we do is guided by core values that shape our editorial
          decisions, our relationships with authors and readers, and our vision
          for the future:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Rigorous scholarship:</strong> We maintain the highest standards
            of academic excellence, ensuring all scholarly work undergoes peer review
            and meets disciplinary standards for research quality
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Accessible communication:</strong> We believe complex ideas can
            and should be communicated clearly, without sacrificing nuance or depth
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Public service:</strong> Knowledge should serve the public good,
            reaching beyond academic circles to inform public discourse and decision-making
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Equity and inclusion:</strong> We actively work to amplify diverse
            voices, remove barriers to publication, and ensure our platform serves
            researchers and readers from all backgrounds
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Transparency:</strong> We're committed to open processes, clear
            communication about our operations, and honest engagement with our community
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Nonprofit Commitment</h2>
        <p>
          LaTech Editorial Publishing operates as a mission-driven organization
          committed to advancing knowledge for the public good. We prioritize
          accessibility, quality, and impact over profit.
        </p>
        <p>
          As we grow, we're working toward formal nonprofit status to ensure our
          mission remains protected and our operations remain transparent. This
          structure allows us to focus entirely on advancing scholarship and
          public understanding, rather than maximizing revenue.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our commitment to open access means we don't charge readers to access
          our content. Our commitment to supporting emerging scholars means we
          don't charge submission fees. Our commitment to quality means we invest
          in rigorous review processes and editorial support.
        </p>
        <p class="disclaimer">
          <strong>Nonprofit status:</strong> in formation / to be announced.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    background-color: var(--color-bg);
    color: var(--color-text);
    padding: var(--spacing-2xl) 0;
    text-align: center;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  .page-header::before {
    display: none;
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xs);
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .page-subtitle {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-text-light);
    margin: 0;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-style: italic;
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
  }

  .page-content {
    padding: var(--spacing-lg) 0 var(--spacing-2xl);
    animation: fadeIn 0.8s ease-out;
  }

  .content-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
  }

  .content-section h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    position: relative;
    display: inline-block;
  }

  .content-section h2::after {
    content: "";
    display: block;
    width: 40px;
    height: 3px;
    background: var(--color-accent);
    margin-top: 5px;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  .content-section ul {
    margin-top: var(--spacing-md);
    padding-left: 0;
    list-style: none;
  }

  .content-section li {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .content-section li::before {
    content: "•";
    color: var(--color-accent);
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    font-weight: bold;
  }

  .disclaimer {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-light);
    font-style: italic;
    background: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    padding: var(--spacing-md);
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent);
  }

  @keyframes fadeIn {
    from {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(10px);
    }
    to {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(0);
    }
  }
</style>
